extends ../layouts/light
block head
	title Coding Style
block main
	main.-codingstyle
		h1 Coding Style
		.content
			.std.pagedescription To see some examples of my coding style depending on the language used you are welcome to check the following projects.
			.row
				.row._sq_nonresize_block
					div
						._title.big.thin.mono Web Apps & Sites
						._lang.bold.mono JADE + SASS + JS
						._description.small To keep my web projects clean, I use only Jade & SASS. I compile them to HTML and CSS using Gulp. I use Vue, React & Riot when needed.
						._example.small
							.bold Example
							span.margin.mono.underlined
								a(href="https://github.com/ivosequeros/ivosequeros.com",target="_blank") This Website
				.row._sq_nonresize_block
					div
						._title.big.thin.mono Javascript Projects
						._lang.bold.mono ES6 with Babel + Frameworks
						._description.small I can use promises, generators, classes, await/async and any other ES2015/17 feature. I mostly use React or Vue.js in my projects.
						._example.small
							.bold Examples
							span.margin.mono.underlined Subtitles Reader
							span &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
							span.margin.mono.underlined Pompeuapi
				.row._sq_nonresize_block
					div
						._title.big.thin.mono Java Projects
						._lang.bold.mono JavaFX, JavaSE or JavaEE
						._description.small Most of the stuff I write in Java is for university. All the classes I write properly follow the OOP Pattern (+ Polymorphism, Inheritance...) and I comment the code as much it needs to be understood by someone else.  I prefer to avoid unnecessary brackets :Pattern
				.row._sq_nonresize_block
					div
						._title.big.thin.mono C++ / C Projects
						._lang.bold.mono Chromium Embedded Framework
						._description.small As with Java, I write in C++ and C mostly for university projects. I properly follow the OOP Pattern in C++ and can use operators and keywords precisely and correctly. I have used both Qt and the Chromium Embedded Framework for User Interfaces.